$values.Body:
<center>Half-Height Example
This map has a tileset that has half-height (.5) units instead of the
standard height (1) and generally offers a more subtle slope and height
difference.  It is NOT recommended that you do this for the whole set,
but to curate specific tiles that you'd like to have more subtle height
changes... or more extreme, by making height changes larger.</center>

<center>Choosing to shrink or expand the Unit Height of a
tileset should be done with some forethought  -  your side texture
will contract or stretch when not set to default and will need to be
accounted for when preparing your structure tiles..</center>

$values.Body:
<center>Verticality
There is a bit of verticality in this map to show off how
layers can stack - designing with verticality in mind will
require a bit of preplanning.  The 'eye' icon in the layer
stack can hide layers individually.</center>
